# <type>(<scope>): <description>
#
# Types:
#   feat     — new feature
#   fix      — bug fix
#   chore    — maintenance (deps, config, CI)
#   docs     — documentation only
#   style    — formatting, no code change
#   refactor — code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   perf     — performance improvement
#   test     — adding or updating tests
#   ci       — CI/CD changes
#   build    — build system or external dependencies
#   revert   — revert a previous commit
#
# Scope (optional): cache, extractor, serve, google-fonts, deps, ci
#
# Examples:
#   feat: add vite 7 support
#   fix(cache): resolve hash collision on concurrent builds
#   chore(deps): update fontext to 1.9
#
# Setup: git config commit.template .gitmessage
